WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:13.584
Everything we've covered, the edge, the stop, the survival
math, the correlations, this one final card ties it all
together into a complete plan you can actually trade.

2
00:00:14.184 --> 00:00:28.032
It's the Grand Recommendation, in Step four's Portfolio
tab. For each appetite, it builds a correlation-aware
basket of moves that genuinely diversify, then runs the
whole basket through the prop simulator together, as one
single portfolio.

3
00:00:28.632 --> 00:00:51.096
Same four appetites you've seen everywhere else, but now
as complete plans. Fastest Growth stacks your highest-edge
moves. Safest picks moves that don't lose together. Best
Overall is the best risk-adjusted blend. And
Professionally weights each move by the inverse of its
volatility, so no single trade can dominate the risk.
That's true risk parity, exactly how a real desk builds
it.

4
00:00:51.696 --> 00:01:04.656
And each plan isn't a guess, it's scored as a whole. Pass
rate, bust rate, expected dollars, Sharpe, drawdown, and
how diversified it truly is. The entire basket, tested
together, not one move at a time.

5
00:01:05.256 --> 00:01:19.944
Click any card, and it draws the combined dollar equity
curve. Every move in the basket, summed day by day, with
your bust line and your day-fourteen risk-of-ruin marker
drawn right on it. You watch the plan survive, or not,
before you ever trade it.

6
00:01:20.544 --> 00:01:28.656
Pick your appetite, hit Apply, and the entire allocation
loads straight into the builder. This is your whole
trading plan, in a single click.

7
00:01:29.256 --> 00:01:32.928
One edge is a trade. This, right here, is a business.
